---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="License — Essenfont"
  description="Essenfont is a mixed-license font. Most donors are OFL-licensed; FSung (Full-Sung) imposes a non-commercial restriction. Each donor's terms are preserved."
  canonical="/license"
>
  <article class="license-page">
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1>Mixed-license font</h1>
    </header>
    <section class="prose">
      <p>
        Essenfont is <strong>not</strong> distributed under a single license.
        It is an assembly of glyphs from multiple donor fonts, each with its
        own license. The assembled font inherits the most restrictive term
        across all donors.
      </p>

      <h2>What that means for you</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>OFL-licensed donors</strong> (Noto, Lentariso, Kedebideri, UniHieroglyphica, etc.) — free to use, study, modify, and redistribute under the <a href="https://openfontlicense.org">SIL Open Font License 1.1</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>FSung-NC</strong> (Full-Sung by F.G. Wang) — <strong>non-commercial use only</strong>. This restriction applies to the CJK glyphs sourced from FSung (CJK Unified Ideographs, Extensions B–G, and related blocks). The build pipeline propagates this restriction into the output font's <code>name</code> table (nameID 0 copyright + nameID 13 license description).</li>
        <li><strong>Synthetic code-chart glyphs</strong> — derived from Unicode Consortium code charts, released under OFL by the build pipeline.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        In practice: you may use Essenfont freely for personal, educational,
        and non-commercial purposes. Commercial use of the CJK portions
        requires separate licensing from the FSung project.
      </p>

      <h2>Per-donor attribution</h2>
      <p>
        Every donor's license is preserved in the font's <code>name</code> table and in the auto-generated <code>LICENSE-SOURCES.md</code>. The build pipeline (in the <a href="https://github.com/essenfont/essenfont">essenfont source repo</a>) refuses to use any donor outside the declared license policy.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
.license-page { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem; }
.page-head { margin-bottom: 2rem; }

h1 { font-family: var(--spec-font-display); font-size: 2rem; }
</style>
